#### A. Memory Management Issues in attrvt.c

**File**: `libxslt/attrvt.c`
**Function**: `xsltSetAttrVTsegment()` (lines ~150-170)

```c
static xsltAttrVTPtr
xsltSetAttrVTsegment(xsltAttrVTPtr avt, void *val) {
    if (avt->nb_seg >= avt->max_seg) {
        size_t size = sizeof(xsltAttrVT) +
                      (avt->max_seg + MAX_AVT_SEG) * sizeof(void *);
	xsltAttrVTPtr tmp = (xsltAttrVTPtr) xmlRealloc(avt, size);
	if (tmp == NULL) {
            xsltFreeAttrVT(avt);  // ← Potential issue here
	    return NULL;
	}
        avt = tmp;
	memset(&avt->segments[avt->nb_seg], 0, MAX_AVT_SEG*sizeof(void *));
	avt->max_seg += MAX_AVT_SEG;
    }
    avt->segments[avt->nb_seg++] = val;
    return avt;
}
```

**Vulnerability**: Use-after-free potential. When `xmlRealloc` fails, the function calls `xsltFreeAttrVT(avt)` which frees the original `avt` pointer, but the caller may still have references to this freed memory.

